g
G(x) = \int_0^xg(y)dy
G'
G''\geq 0
 G'
x<c_{x,y}<y<c_{y,z}<z
x<y<z\implies \frac{G(y)-G(x)}{y-x} = G'(c_{x,y})\le G'(c_{y,z})=\frac{G(z)-G(y)}{z-y} 
 (z-y+y-x)G(y) \le (y-x)G(z) + (z-y)G(x)\\ G(y)\le \frac{y-x}{z-x} G(z)+  \frac{z-y}{z-x} G(x) 
t\in (0,1)
y=(z-x)t+x = (1-t)x+tz\in (x,z)
 G((1-t)x+tz)=G(y)\le \frac{y-x}{z-x} G(z)+  \frac{z-y}{z-x} G(x) = t G(z)+  (1-t) G(x). 
